parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Insufficient Rear Air Conditioning Air Flow
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate air flow from the rear air conditioning vents can cause the rear compartment to become extremely hot, potentially leading to heat stroke or discomfort for passengers, especially children.
symptoms: Little to no air flow from the rear air conditioning vents
cool air but very slow or light flow
rear compartment becomes extremely hot
passengers in the back cannot feel the air.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Air Conditioning Evaporator Fan Design Flaw
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the rear air conditioning evaporator fan without an air filter can cause the evaporator vanes to become clogged with dust and debris, leading to system failure and costly repairs.
symptoms: Reduced air flow from the rear air conditioning vents
failure of the rear air conditioning system
expensive repair bills.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the check engine light to come on and may lead to expensive repairs, potentially affecting the vehicle's performance and emissions.
symptoms: Check engine light comes on
diagnosed as catalytic converter failure
expensive repair costs.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure Affecting Instrument Cluster and Braking System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the instrument cluster to malfunction, leading to the loss of critical information such as speed and odometer readings, and can also affect the braking system, causing the brake pedal to extend to the floor, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The instrument cluster malfunctions
the check engine warning light illuminates
the speedometer and odometer become inoperable
unknown warning lights illuminate
the brake pedal extends to the floor while depressed
the brakes become inoperable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped front brake rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate violently when braking, especially at high speeds, which can lead to loss of control and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or vibrates violently when braking
especially at high speeds (above 60 mph)
the steering wheel shakes or vibrates
the brake pedal pulsates
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking.
